Bat populations in Scotland and Britain have declined significantly in the last century.
They are threatened by construction and development that affect litters and habitat loss.
Windmills and lights also pose risks, as do fly duct tape and some chemical treatments on building materials, as well as attacks on domestic cats.
Bats aren't actually blind.
